speaker.bio: Christine is from Omaha, Nebraska where she works as a full stack Ruby on Rails engineer at Flywheel, Delightful Wordpress Hosting for Creatives. She has 12 years experience as a Java engineer with a focus on APIs, testing, and micro-services (before they were cool). Then to change it up, she took the plunge into Ruby in 2018. In her spare time she is an avid reader, huge Rush fan and is attempting to work through the primary Ashtanga yoga series.
speaker.title: You don’t know ML and neither do we
speaker.description: But that’s fine, Google does! Google Cloud Vision AI is an approachable collection of deep learning algorithms that enables high quality visual analysis on any application.  But will the actual analysis meet your expectations? Finding millions of images to put Cloud Vision through its paces is just an Instagram away. With both Cloud Vision and Instagram in combination, this talk will show the highs and lows of using this advanced imaging technology, no data science degree required.
